p: Supporting this, a Sanofi Pasteur integrated immunogenicity analysis across 10 phase II and 6 phase III trials undertaken in dengue endemic and non-endemic countries confirmed that Geometric Mean Titers (GMTs) were positively influenced by baseline dengue seropositivity: participants who were seropositive to at least one dengue serotype at baseline in general achieved higher post-dose 3 GMTs for all serotypes than those who were seronegative regardless of the region [ 36].
